Nigerian actor, Yul Edochie, is grateful to God for life. In a recent Instagram post, the former gubernatorial aspirant says that he was on his way to the East from Lagos when his car had an accident along Ore- Benin expressway but sustained non-life threatening injuries. Ore road is famed as one of the ‘killer roads’ in Nigeria. Read his post below: <img class="aligncenter wp-image-941027 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1863" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie.jpg 720w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-411x598.jpg 411w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-383x557.jpg 383w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-165x240.jpg 165w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-330x480.jpg 330w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-412x600.jpg 412w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-941028 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1881" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2.jpg 720w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2-407x598.jpg 407w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2-379x557.jpg 379w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2-163x240.jpg 163w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2-327x480.jpg 327w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Yul-Edochie-2-408x600.jpg 408w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />